<tool id="splitChromosome" name="Split BAM to Chromosomes" version="1.0.1">
  <description>splits BAM file to individual BAM files per chromosome</description>
  <command interpreter="python">
    splitChromosome.py
      --input1=$input1
  </command>
  <inputs>
    <param name="input1" type="data" format="bam" label="BAM File to Convert" />
  </inputs>
  <outputs>
    <data format="bam" name="output1" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm1 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output2" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm2 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output3" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm3 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output4" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm4 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output5" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm5 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output6" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm6 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output7" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm7 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output8" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm8 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output9" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm9 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output10" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm10 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output11" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm11 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output12" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm12 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output13" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm13 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output14" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm14 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output15" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm15 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output16" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm16 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output17" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm17 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output18" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm18 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output19" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm19 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output20" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm20 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output21" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm21 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output22" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm22 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="output23" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: Chrm23 BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="outputX" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: ChrmX BAM" />
    <data format="bam" name="outputY" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: ChrmY BAM" />
  </outputs>
  <help>

**What it does**

The splitChromosome option on the bam executable splits an indexed BAM file into multiple files based on the Chromosome (Reference Name).
The files all have the same base name, but with an _# where # corresponds with the associated reference id from the BAM file.
  </help>
</tool>
